message: /* Business career */  Added SALN filing in 2012
Conversion from sq km to sq mi is wrong. 1 mi = 1.806 km but 1 sq mi = 2.589 sq km
/* Political Influence */  corrected to actual value as indicated in the referenced link
Correct the name of Amando Doronila
Sanitized and removed biased religious undertones; added additioanal and posted emblem
Updated Info Summary to feature both Info Summary from the Scarborough Shoal wiki page and the Macclesfield wiki page.
/* Political influence in the Philippines */  Grammar correction.
/* Background information */  - Added Punta, Sta. Ana Chapel
Revert to the more comprehensive version
/* Structure of the Iglesia ni Cristo */  - increase font size to 90% to show formatting (bold letters) and improve overall look
/* Structure of the Iglesia ni Cristo */  - corrected tense; also, ''task'' is more appropriate than ''right'' as they believe that this is an exclusive mandate
''First'' Executive Minister is not accurate; doctrinally, the INCs believe, Apostle James was also an Executive Minister, so Manalo could not be the first.
Statement vague. He served as what?
Secular sources not fitting, since religious sources from other denominations also recognize him as such. I used the term "widely recognized" because only a small group does not believe so.
/* Structure of the Iglesia ni Cristo */  restored hierarch, set in a box
What accounts for a credible proof? As long as the sources cannot be disputed, I guess the reference should remain.
/* Organizations */  - Binhi is literally just the seed; 'seedling' is a young plant
/* Politics */  - added source on INC vote conversion
Reverted; discuss in talk page which item do you think is allegation and which you think is not; as it is, you have no particulars and it is not a justification for deleting the whole article
Revert; Antonio Abaya's article has no bearing in the article
Reverted; CNN indeed does not dispute Doronilla's account; Abaya's article makes no reference to Doronilla's book; rather it is a different article
Should go to Armando Doronilla article, not here;  if sources are to be justified everytime, article will be cluttered with unrelated stories
Birth dates are no longer wikilinked
